libeasyfc
------------------------------------------
libeasyfc is an interface library to generate fontconfig configuration for
user preferences. this supports to assign your preferrable fonts to the alias
fonts, such as sans-serif, serif and monospace per languages.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.25-1
  gettext-0.18.1.1-2
  girepository-GLib2.0-1.36.0-1
  girepository-x11-1.36.0-1
  libbz2-devel-1.0.6-2
  libeasyfc-devel-0.13.0-1bl1
  libeasyfc0-0.13.0-1bl1
  libexpat-devel-2.1.0-3
  libffi-devel-3.0.13-1
  libfontconfig-devel-2.10.93-1
  libfontconfig1-2.10.93-1
  libfreetype-devel-2.4.12-1
  libfreetype6-2.4.12-1
  libglib2.0-devel-2.36.4-1
  libglib2.0_0-2.36.4-1
  libharfbuzz-devel-0.9.19-1
  libharfbuzz0-0.9.19-1
  libiconv-1.14-2
  liblzma-devel-5.0.2_20110517-1
  libpcre-devel-8.33-1
  libxml2-2.9.1-1
  libxml2-devel-2.9.1-1
  zlib-devel-1.2.8-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.23.51-1
  cygport-0.13.0-1
  gcc-core-4.7.3-1
  gobject-introspection-1.36.0-1
  libtool-2.4-1
  make-3.82.90-1

Canonical website:
  http://tagoh.bitbucket.org/libeasyfc/

Canonical download:
  https://bitbucket.org/tagoh/libeasyfc/downloads/libeasyfc-0.13.0.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack libeasyfc-0.13.0-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
         unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./libeasyfc-0.13.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libeasyfc-0.13.0-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libeasyfc-0.13.0-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libeasyfc0-0.13.0-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libeasyfc-devel-0.13.0-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/girepository-Easyfc0.12-0.13.0-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

